solution:
**A. Mapping.**
```json
PUT /farmers
{
  "mappings": {
    "properties": {
      "personalId":  { "type": "keyword" },
      "name":        { "type": "text" },
      "surname":     { "type": "text" },
      "age":         { "type": "integer" },
      "address":     { "type": "text" },
      "state":       { "type": "keyword" },
      "biography":   { "type": "text" },
      "experienced": { "type": "boolean" }
    }
  }
}
```
`personalId`/`state` are `keyword` (exact-match identifiers/enums, not analyzed); `name`, `surname`, `biography` are `text` (analyzed, full-text searchable — `biography` in particular needs the standard analyzer to support the token-based query in part B); `age` is `integer`; `experienced` is `boolean`.

**B. Query.** Name/must-match terms go in `must` (mandatory, contribute to score), the exclusion goes in `must_not` (filtering, not scored), and the score boost for an *optional* extra term goes in `should` (only affects relevance score, not inclusion):
```json
GET /farmers/_search
{
  "query": {
    "bool": {
      "must": [
        { "match": { "name": "Bill" } },
        { "match": { "biography": "cactus" } },
        { "match": { "biography": "aloe" } }
      ],
      "must_not": [
        { "match": { "biography": "potato" } }
      ],
      "should": [
        { "match": { "biography": "crop" } }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```
Documents matching a `should` clause on top of the mandatory `must` clauses get a **higher relevance score** (thanks to TF/IDF-BM25 contribution of the extra matched clause), exactly implementing "assign a higher score if 'crop' is found", without making it a requirement for inclusion in the result set.

**A. Collections.** **Four collections**, one per entity — `farmers`, `farms`, `animals`, `crops` — since each is an independently identified, independently queried concept with (at most) many-to-many or 1-to-N relations to the others; none of them is a small, always-accessed-together dependent of another, so full embedding of one inside another would duplicate data unnecessarily and blow up document size for the continuously-growing sides.

**B. Relations.** Each many-to-N / N-to-N relationship (*Work*: Farmer 1–2 Farms; *House*: Animal exactly 1 Farm, with `housingDate`; *Cultivate*: Farmer N–M Crop, with `plantingDate`) is implemented with **references** (the `_id` of the related document), embedding the relationship's own attributes (if any) next to the reference:

```json
// farmers
{
  "_id": ObjectId("..."),
  "personalId": "P001",
  "name": "Rick",
  "surname": "Sanchez",
  "age": 70,
  "address": "12 Portal St",
  "state": "Lombardy",
  "biography": "...",
  "experienced": true,
  "farmIds": [ ObjectId("farmA"), ObjectId("farmB") ]   // Work: 1..2 farms
}

// farms
{
  "_id": ObjectId("farmA"),
  "name": "Green Valley",
  "address": "3 Field Rd",
  "state": "Lombardy",
  "description": "Organic mixed farm"
}

// animals
{
  "_id": ObjectId("..."),
  "tag": "A123",
  "name": "Bessy",
  "age": 4,
  "animalType": "Cow",
  "breed": "Holstein",
  "farmId": ObjectId("farmA"),          // House: each animal housed by exactly 1 farm
  "housingDate": ISODate("2023-05-01")
}

// crops
{
  "_id": ObjectId("..."),
  "productId": "CR009",
  "name": "Tomato",
  "quantity": 500,
  "expirationDate": ISODate("2025-12-01"),
  "plantingSeason": "summer",
  "growthTime": 3,
  "cultivatedBy": [
    { "farmerId": ObjectId("..."), "plantingDate": ISODate("2025-03-10") }
  ]
}
```
Each animal carries a single `farmId` (1:1 on the animal side of *House*), each farmer carries up to two `farmIds` (1..2 on the farmer side of *Work*), and each crop carries an array `cultivatedBy` of `{farmerId, plantingDate}` (N:M *Cultivate*).

**C. Crops cultivated per farmer named "Rick", ≥ 20 crops.**
```javascript
db.crops.aggregate([
  { $unwind: "$cultivatedBy" },
  { $lookup: {
      from: "farmers",
      localField: "cultivatedBy.farmerId",
      foreignField: "_id",
      as: "farmer"
  }},
  { $unwind: "$farmer" },
  { $match: { "farmer.name": "Rick" } },
  { $group: {
      _id: "$farmer._id",
      farmerName: { $first: "$farmer.name" },
      totalCrops: { $sum: 1 }
  }},
  { $match: { totalCrops: { $gte: 20 } } }
])
```

**D. Farms housing ≥ 10 cows of ≥ 5 different breeds.**
```javascript
db.animals.aggregate([
  { $match: { animalType: "Cow" } },
  { $group: {
      _id: "$farmId",
      cowCount: { $sum: 1 },
      breeds: { $addToSet: "$breed" }
  }},
  { $addFields: { breedCount: { $size: "$breeds" } } },
  { $match: { cowCount: { $gte: 10 }, breedCount: { $gte: 5 } } },
  { $count: "totalFarms" }
])
```
